column1: Br Silk Screen (kt file pin name)

column10: There should be a note on the Br schematic bottom side connectors saying:
The silk screen matches the pin numbers for the top side connectors.
So they are all off by one on the bottom side:
Odd numbered pins have a silkscreen that is one less
Even numbered pins have a silkscreen that is one greater
Or saying it the another way:
The numbers on the bottom side silk screen are swapped relative to the connector pinout,
e.g. B4 is actually B3, B6 is actually B5 and vice-versa
Warning, Bank B connector J7 has some very funky pin numbering weirdness on pins 33,34,35,36
Pinouts for Alchitry Br Breakout board
